reviews.text: Had a great time with the family after some extensive shopping! Service was fantastic! The waitress was super friendly and accommodating! The food was delicious! I wouldn't say it was "authentic Mexican", but it was really good nonetheless! Definitely get the fundido with the turkey chorizo, so good! The difference options of guacamole was awesome too! Really loved the roasted pepper guac! Fun atmosphere and a good patio too. Was able to get right in at 2pm on a Saturday.

Delicious food and friendly service. My husband and I split taco choices so we each got to try the duck, portobello, and angus carne asada tacos (as in order in my picture). Highly recommend all 3! So glad we stopped in!

Food was amazing! We had the queso dip, carne asada fajitas and the southwest salad. Everything was delicious and fresh! The home made salsas were so good, we had to buy some to go! Service was amazing as well, both our original waitress and waiter, once we were transferred during shift change , were great!

I had an incredible experience at Taqueria 27! The food was fresh, flavorful, and came out fast ‚Äî but what really made the visit memorable was our server, Chloe. She was absolutely amazing! Super friendly, attentive, and made us feel welcome from the moment we sat down. Chloe had great menu recommendations and kept everything running smoothly the entire time. You can tell she genuinely cares about the customer experience. Definitely ask for Chloe if you go ‚Äî she‚Äôll make your night! Can‚Äôt wait to come back!

Our food was flavorful and the meat tender.  The multi cheese queso with mole rojo was delicious and since it was on a flame it stayed warm the whole meal. The chipotle salsa was awesome! Lastly our server Chloe was so kind and knowledgeable giving great recommendations for our dinner.  She deserves a raise!

recentReviews.text: Truly enjoyed the range of delicious hot sauces to that were shared with us tonight.  JC did a great job taking care of us and we even got to meet el gran jefe Miles.  Very personable team at this place.  Four different dishes were all perfect for the person that received it.  Whatever the opposite of bland is, this place is it.  Can you say delicioso?
Food is great. I always want to Venture out and get something new, but I always come back to the Carne Asada burrito.  Service was the best! Chloe took care of us.
So good! Been here twice in 3 days. Definitely our favorite. Please open one in St. George Utah!
I got the Brent tacos and I got rice on the side and it was cold. And I also asked for corn instead of flour tortillas and they gave me flour. But besides that it was good.

I was totally shocked that I found something new.... it's so rare to surprise me with food. I had the duck. And the pork bellies. All were great, the rice has a good flavor, didn't like the beans.
Prices were a little high for tacos. $6 each. But I really appreciated a great Mew food experience. Sophie handled us and a big table very well. She was a good server. I will come here again!!!

detailedReviews.text:
Fantastic Dining Experience!

We had a wonderful meal here! The service was excellent‚Äîour server was kind, attentive, and even brought a sample of the enchilada sauce to make sure it wasn‚Äôt too spicy for me, which I really appreciated.

We started with the shrimp bites appetizer‚Äîabsolutely delicious! The balsamic glaze was divine and complemented the shrimp perfectly. I ordered the spring enchiladas and loved every bite. The flavors were fresh, and the small side salad was a lovely touch.

The atmosphere was beautiful and added to the overall experience. Our server made the evening feel warm and fun. I would definitely recommend this place and look forward to coming back!

detailedReviews.author: Kevin Frost
detailedReviews.text: I would never come back here. The tacos were mediocre at best, our appetizer was burnt, the server was inattentive, the dessert was obviously just taken from a freezer and thrown in a microwave, and they charged $4 for a tiny cup of rice and beans. What kind of a place charges for rice and beans when you're getting tacos? Especially $4 and for a tiny scoop of each? All the server said when we ordered the tacos was "would you like rice and beans on the side?" No indication that it was going to be an extra $8 for our two orders!
